cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use zer0lint, please cite it as below."
title: "zer0lint: extraction-health diagnostics for mem0 and HTTP memory endpoints"
abstract: >-
  zer0lint is a memory-extraction diagnostic that injects synthetic facts into mem0
  (or any HTTP add/search memory endpoint) and judges whether they survive the LLM
  extraction step by round-trip recall, then generates and validates a stronger
  extraction prompt before writing it to config.
type: software
version: 0.2.1
authors:
